1
00:00:15,340 --> 00:00:17,350
Ayumi, let's give it another go.

2
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:21,650
Us, I mean.

3
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:27,890
I think as we are now, we can make it work.

4
00:00:29,810 --> 00:00:33,600
Both you and I have changed.

5
00:00:35,950 --> 00:00:38,020
We won't repeat the same mistakes.

6
00:00:51,070 --> 00:00:52,140
I'm home.

7
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:53,880
Welcome back.

8
00:01:00,050 --> 00:01:02,430
- Hey there.
- Hey.

9
00:01:02,430 --> 00:01:06,100
Guess what? Eggs were on sale today.

10
00:01:07,120 --> 00:01:08,720
And look.

11
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,280
I found your favorite chocolate bar.

12
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:13,560
- Thanks.
- You have a sweet tooth, right?

13
00:01:14,270 --> 00:01:17,910
To tell you the truth, no.

14
00:01:17,910 --> 00:01:19,940
Wait, really?

15
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:21,800
Yeah. Sweets aren't my thing.

16
00:01:24,700 --> 00:01:26,410
More for me, then.

17
00:01:26,410 --> 00:01:28,570
I appreciate the thought though.

18
00:01:31,870 --> 00:01:34,250
What's your schedule tomorrow? More interviews?

19
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:36,790
Yup. I hope they'll go well.

20
00:01:36,790 --> 00:01:40,440
You'll do great, I guarantee it.

21
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:43,390
Say you can cook any cuisine. It's your biggest selling point.

22
00:01:43,970 --> 00:01:45,590
I'll make sure to make a point of that.

23
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:50,170
- Thanks for dinner.
- Sure.

24
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:00,850
- It's good!
- Thank god.

25
00:02:00,850 --> 00:02:02,610
Yeah, this is delicious.

26
00:02:03,180 --> 00:02:05,360
Let me give it a try for myself.

27
00:02:10,150 --> 00:02:12,170
Yeah, that's good.

28
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:16,960
- What about you?
- Hm?

29
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:19,220
What were you up to today?

30
00:02:20,810 --> 00:02:26,490
First, I went to get groceries. Then, I went to the bank.

31
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:31,110
And finally, I dropped off my comforters at the dry cleaner's.

32
00:02:31,110 --> 00:02:32,860
It was a busy day, I tell you.

33
00:02:32,860 --> 00:02:36,350
So much for taking a vacation from work.

34
00:02:36,350 --> 00:02:38,920
- I keep finding more to do.
- I see.

35
00:02:40,530 --> 00:02:42,780
- Ayumi.
- Yeah?

36
00:02:42,780 --> 00:02:47,310
Let me know if you need help organizing your resume, okay?

37
00:02:47,310 --> 00:02:53,710
I can give you tips as an experienced office worker.

38
00:02:53,710 --> 00:02:55,310
Thanks.

39
00:02:55,310 --> 00:03:00,000
Here, let me walk you through an interview, too.

40
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:04,470
First, you knock not two, but three times,
and greet your interviewers.

41
00:03:04,470 --> 00:03:06,350
Now this is the important part.

42
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:09,080
Only sit down when they invite you to.
It's business etiquette.

43
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:12,690
- I know.
- You know? Great.

44
00:03:12,690 --> 00:03:16,220
I've been through my fair share of interviews,

45
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:19,440
- so let me know if you need advice.
- Thanks, but I'm doing fine.

46
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:20,880
Right, I figured.

47
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:26,050
- I'll come visit again.
- Sure.

48
00:03:26,050 --> 00:03:28,260
I'll be waiting with dinner ready tomorrow.

49
00:03:28,260 --> 00:03:29,940
Good luck.

50
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:33,480
You got this.

51
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:35,010
Thanks. See you tomorrow.

52
00:03:36,950 --> 00:03:39,360
You can do it.

53
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,050
[Resume: Ayumi Yamagishi]

54
00:03:42,550 --> 00:03:45,640
- Have a seat.
- Thank you.

55
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:50,640
So before, you worked as a clerk?

56
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:54,570
Yes. I worked as a receptionist in an office building.

57
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:57,560
And now you're hoping to get into the restaurant industry?

58
00:03:57,560 --> 00:04:00,620
That's quite a career change.

59
00:04:01,740 --> 00:04:06,840
I have a passion for cooking,
and hope to one day open a place of my own.

60
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:10,620
As such, I'd like to gain experience cooking
in a professional kitchen.

61
00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:15,180
So you're jumping careers at your age?

62
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:17,120
Yes, I suppose I am.

63
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:21,950
Do you have any experience cooking commercially?
Like at a part-time job, for example.

64
00:04:21,950 --> 00:04:25,900
I do not. However, I cook for myself every day at home.

65
00:04:25,900 --> 00:04:27,610
I hope to one day obtain a culinary certification as well.

66
00:04:27,610 --> 00:04:32,240
Cooking at home and prepping for a restaurant
are two entirely different skillsets.

67
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:35,810
Restaurant prep demands speed and efficiency above all else.

68
00:04:35,810 --> 00:04:41,050
I'm sorry, but I don't think this is the place for you.

69
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:43,040
I understand.

70
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:46,990
[Places I've Applied To]

71
00:04:46,990 --> 00:04:49,120
[Yellowtail - 620 Yen]

72
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:52,440
I never realized how pricy yellowtail was.

73
00:04:55,550 --> 00:04:57,560
I'm doing some afternoon shopping today.

74
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:01,000
It's not like I have spare time though.

75
00:05:05,420 --> 00:05:11,520
I'm just taking some time off for myself.

76
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:13,170
There, take one.

77
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:22,080
Sir, I have no time to cook such a time-consuming dish.
[Stewed Yellowtail and Daikon]

78
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:25,620
- No time at all!
- Is that so? Then I'll take it back...

79
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,880
Oh?

80
00:05:31,980 --> 00:05:34,150
Sure, it's a pain having him around.

81
00:05:34,150 --> 00:05:37,650
But without him, the office feels empty, you know?

82
00:05:38,290 --> 00:05:40,710
So you miss him?

83
00:05:40,710 --> 00:05:42,430
Not at all.

84
00:05:42,430 --> 00:05:46,500
It just feels like someone deleted my go-to
"cute pets" compilation video.

85
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,440
Personally, I'd miss that.

86
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,720
Well, I wouldn't.

87
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:53,400
- I don't believe you...
- Shirosaki! Minamikawa!

88
00:05:54,450 --> 00:05:55,800
Yes, sir?

89
00:05:57,750 --> 00:06:02,160
Ebihara's allowed to come back to the office again.

90
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:06,470
- Really?
- That's great news.

91
00:06:06,470 --> 00:06:08,750
You're telling me.

92
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:13,240
I can only imagine how depressed he is now, with nothing to do.

93
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:28,730
Four tablespoons of soy sauce, mirin,

94
00:06:28,730 --> 00:06:30,530
and sake.

95
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:33,600
Then add the daikon...

96
00:06:38,930 --> 00:06:41,190
Just perfect.

97
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:47,300
[Incoming call from: Yoko Ebihara]

98
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:50,790
- Hello?
- Katsuo!

99
00:06:50,790 --> 00:06:55,430
- Yeah, what's up?
- Matori wanted us to give you a call.

100
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:56,920
I see.

101
00:06:56,920 --> 00:07:00,580
Hey... I ran out of rice.

102
00:07:01,740 --> 00:07:03,020
Hey.

103
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:07,350
Fine.

104
00:07:07,350 --> 00:07:10,480
Oh, grab me another serving as well.

105
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,940
There you go.

106
00:07:13,290 --> 00:07:16,530
Matori says she misses you, Katsuo.

107
00:07:16,530 --> 00:07:19,820
Katsuo, look!

108
00:07:19,820 --> 00:07:21,410
You got yourself a backpack?

109
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:23,940
Grandma and Grandpa bought it for me.

110
00:07:23,940 --> 00:07:25,970
We went shopping for it together today.

111
00:07:25,970 --> 00:07:27,510
Yeah? Good for you, Matori.

112
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:30,420
Come visit, Katsuo!

113
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:32,890
I'd love to, but I can't exactly visit now.

114
00:07:32,890 --> 00:07:37,670
Work keeps him busy. Isn't that right, Katsuo?

115
00:07:37,670 --> 00:07:39,520
Yeah.

116
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:42,220
Real busy.

117
00:07:42,910 --> 00:07:44,590
Are you home now?

118
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:48,420
Working at home certainly sounds rough.

119
00:07:48,420 --> 00:07:52,260
Come visit the family in Oita again. We all miss you!

120
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:54,120
- Sure thing.
- Hey.

121
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:57,760
Your rice. Is that enough?

122
00:07:57,760 --> 00:08:00,450
Yes, thank you.

123
00:08:00,450 --> 00:08:02,500
We'll talk again, Katsuo.

124
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,100
Hey, wait!

125
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:06,160
- Bye-bye!
- Let me -

126
00:08:24,300 --> 00:08:26,780
Fill out our survey,

127
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:30,530
and you might win a prize.

128
00:08:30,530 --> 00:08:32,710
We'd appreciate your time and assistance.

129
00:08:32,710 --> 00:08:34,570
I'll fill out a survey.

130
00:08:34,570 --> 00:08:36,200
- Thank you so much.
- No problem.

131
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:39,050
[Survey]

132
00:08:42,010 --> 00:08:45,130
[Profession]

133
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:56,340
- I'm back.
- Welcome back.

134
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:58,440
Phew...

135
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:03,600
How'd your interviews go?

136
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,620
I think they were all a bust.

137
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:08,340
That's too bad...

138
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:09,770
- Alright, onto the next.
-

139
00:09:09,770 --> 00:09:11,830
You have more chances. You got this.

140
00:09:11,830 --> 00:09:15,890
Dinner's almost ready, so eat and prep for tomorrow, yeah?

141
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:17,600
That's the plan.

142
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:21,000
- Stewed yellowtail and daikon?
- Yeah.

143
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,400
- I'll help.
- Thanks.

144
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:41,550
- Thank you for dinner.
- Thank you for helping.

145
00:09:47,350 --> 00:09:51,140
- That's delicious.
- Yes!

146
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:52,350
It's so good.

147
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:53,740
- Really?
- Really.

148
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:55,710
- Awesome.
- The flavors seeped in well.

149
00:09:55,710 --> 00:09:58,130
Let me give this a taste...

150
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,500
That's good.

151
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,240
Perfect, even.

152
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:16,950
- Ayumi.
- Yeah?

153
00:10:18,310 --> 00:10:20,570
Don't ever feel like you need to push yourself, okay?

154
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:23,710
Right now, I'm here for you, too.

155
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:28,640
So while costs might rack up for you,

156
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:33,650
I can pay rent for us here, if you decide to move back in.

157
00:10:33,650 --> 00:10:36,330
I'll make sure to earn enough for the two of us.

158
00:10:36,330 --> 00:10:38,390
So you can live without worry, okay?

159
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:44,080
I want to support you.

160
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,710
In every aspect of the word.

161
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:49,520
So if you're ever in a bind, tell me. Okay?

162
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:52,110
I will. Thank you.

163
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:02,710
These daikon turned out delicious.

164
00:11:02,710 --> 00:11:04,000
What's up?

165
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,240
Sorry for bothering you when you're busy.

166
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:12,150
I heard you'd booked a nice restaurant for my birthday.

167
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:16,320
I know you worked several part time gigs
to afford the place, too.

168
00:11:20,030 --> 00:11:21,780
I'm sorry.

169
00:11:22,430 --> 00:11:26,390
I never noticed you were pushing yourself like that.

170
00:11:27,620 --> 00:11:34,080
My motto has always been the one with money foots the bill.

171
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:39,510
I didn't even realize that was only adding pressure to you.

172
00:11:41,570 --> 00:11:45,880
Tsubaki, when we're together,

173
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:48,990
I always have to act like I'm more than I actually am.

174
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:56,190
You're an amazing woman who does good work,
and owns her own company.

175
00:11:56,190 --> 00:11:59,610
Meanwhile, I struggle to make a living even for myself.

176
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:04,150
We're not made for each other, Tsubaki.

177
00:12:05,180 --> 00:12:07,910
There are better people out there for you.

178
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:13,640
According to who?

179
00:12:15,350 --> 00:12:20,730
Who out there is judging our worth to each other?

180
00:12:23,110 --> 00:12:28,350
I don't want some stranger to make that decision for us.

181
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:34,320
If you no longer love me, then there's nothing more I can do.

182
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:38,110
But if that's not the case,

183
00:12:39,140 --> 00:12:41,550
then I want us to stay together, Ryo.

184
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:47,150
I want to strive to stay together with you.

185
00:12:50,490 --> 00:12:54,100
Sorry, I'm keeping the guys waiting.

186
00:13:13,410 --> 00:13:15,090
[Koenji Junjo Shopping Street]

187
00:13:15,090 --> 00:13:17,230
- More interviews today, Ayumi?
- Yup.

188
00:13:17,230 --> 00:13:19,380
I also wish you the best at the office today.

189
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:20,750
Thanks.

190
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:22,590
- Then I'm headed this way.
- Take care.

191
00:13:22,590 --> 00:13:25,520
- Good luck with your interviews.
- Thanks.

192
00:13:27,350 --> 00:13:30,620
Remember, Ayumi. If you're in a bind, tell me.

193
00:13:30,620 --> 00:13:34,040
Thanks, I'm doing just fine. See you later.

194
00:13:36,330 --> 00:13:38,670
Morning.

195
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:40,770
Good morning.

196
00:13:40,770 --> 00:13:42,990
- Good morning.
- Morning.

197
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:45,240
Morning, Chief.

198
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:48,580
I bet vacation bored you out of your mind.

199
00:13:48,580 --> 00:13:50,520
How did you spend your time, sir?

200
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:54,580
I was real busy.

201
00:13:54,580 --> 00:13:57,940
There was so much to do around the house.

202
00:13:57,940 --> 00:14:01,270
Every day was jam-packed with activities.

203
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:03,220
I was busy as can be.

204
00:14:03,220 --> 00:14:05,500
Ebihara, could you summarize our progress thus far?

205
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:06,830
Of course.

206
00:14:06,830 --> 00:14:12,110
Actually, I was handling most of the work,
so I will give a summary.

207
00:14:12,110 --> 00:14:15,490
Don't worry, I was given the brief. I've got this.

208
00:14:15,490 --> 00:14:17,260
- Thank you, sir. But worry not,
- Allow me to...

209
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:18,900
I will handle this.

210
00:14:19,660 --> 00:14:22,030
Now then, allow me to summarize.

211
00:14:23,710 --> 00:14:25,380
I'm sorry that got a bit lengthy.

212
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:27,070
No worries at all.

213
00:14:27,070 --> 00:14:29,640
Yanagisawa, could I have a minute?

214
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:31,430
If it's urgent, please just send me an email.

215
00:14:31,430 --> 00:14:33,780
My throat is sore from all that talking.

216
00:14:37,590 --> 00:14:41,400
I really think clientele feedback could bolster our proposal.

217
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:44,490
So if we could focus on these surveys...

218
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:46,050
Ebihara.

219
00:14:46,050 --> 00:14:47,860
- Could I speak my mind?
- Sure.

220
00:14:47,860 --> 00:14:51,990
Our priority now is selling our bigwigs on this product,
not our clients.

221
00:14:51,990 --> 00:14:55,880
So first, we have to get our proposal through, alright?

222
00:15:02,460 --> 00:15:03,680
Experience cooking professionally?

223
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:07,280
No, our place requires no such thing.

224
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:09,640
- Really?
- Of course.

225
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:13,730
You would start by working as one of our waitresses.

226
00:15:13,730 --> 00:15:17,010
I think our attire will suit you perfectly.

227
00:15:17,010 --> 00:15:19,900
When can I schedule your first shift?

228
00:15:26,780 --> 00:15:31,690
How was your first day back at the office?

229
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:37,050
It was great.

230
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:41,920
We had a meeting for the project I'm working on.

231
00:15:42,660 --> 00:15:45,590
My throat's a bit sore from all the talking.

232
00:15:45,590 --> 00:15:47,920
- I see.
- Yeah.

233
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:54,690
How were your interviews?

234
00:15:55,680 --> 00:15:58,230
I haven't heard back from any place yet,

235
00:15:58,230 --> 00:16:00,250
but I think they'll all turn me down.

236
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:04,080
I see. There's always a next time.

237
00:16:06,540 --> 00:16:09,260
- That's too bad though.
- Yeah.

238
00:16:16,450 --> 00:16:19,460
- Katsuo.
- What's up?

239
00:16:21,070 --> 00:16:24,150
I think I'll open my own restaurant.

240
00:16:25,970 --> 00:16:27,640
- Your own restaurant?
- Yeah.

241
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:31,650
I was thinking about asking Taihei if I could rent his bar space.

242
00:16:31,650 --> 00:16:34,560
His place only opens in the evening,
[ONBORO]

243
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:37,370
so I thought maybe I could use the space during the day.

244
00:16:40,890 --> 00:16:42,720
That's a great idea.

245
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:46,270
I haven't consulted with Taihei about it yet though.

246
00:16:46,270 --> 00:16:48,510
I'm looking forward to it.

247
00:16:50,290 --> 00:16:52,340
I'll help in any way I can.

248
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:54,190
Thanks.

249
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:57,690
I'll do what I can for you, too.

250
00:16:57,690 --> 00:17:00,000
- For me?
- Yeah.

251
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:03,190
You had a bad day at work today, didn't you?

252
00:17:03,190 --> 00:17:04,780
What? How...

253
00:17:04,780 --> 00:17:06,920
You're an open book.

254
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:15,640
Speak up if you're also ever in a bind, okay?

255
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:17,850
Yeah.

256
00:17:19,260 --> 00:17:20,830
I'm doing fine.

257
00:17:38,910 --> 00:17:41,190
So, what did you need to ask?
[Finale: Change Caused by Clumsy Love!]

258
00:17:41,190 --> 00:17:44,880
Okay, here I go. Taihei.

259
00:17:45,770 --> 00:17:49,900
Please let me rent your bar space in the afternoons.

260
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:51,900
- Huh?
- Rent this space?

261
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:57,950
Yeah. I want to use this space
to run a Mexican restaurant in the afternoons.

262
00:17:59,470 --> 00:18:05,230
Not immediately, though.
Only after I've saved up enough money.

263
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:09,060
Of course, I'll make sure to keep the space clean for you.

264
00:18:09,060 --> 00:18:12,630
I want us to discuss a rental fee
that works for the both of us, too.

265
00:18:12,630 --> 00:18:15,810
So please, help me make this a reality.

266
00:18:19,330 --> 00:18:21,970
Sounds fine by me. What do you think?

267
00:18:23,650 --> 00:18:27,970
Yeah, I don't mind.
I'm not using this space for anything else in the afternoons.

268
00:18:27,970 --> 00:18:30,230
- You mean it?
- Of course.

269
00:18:30,230 --> 00:18:31,520
Thank you so much.

270
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:32,960
I'll call our landlord about it, too.

271
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:34,910
Thank you.

272
00:18:35,990 --> 00:18:41,120
Yes. We believe user feedback is crucial to this project.

273
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,950
Yes, please.

274
00:18:42,950 --> 00:18:45,580
We would appreciate any assistance from your branch...

275
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:54,090
[Surveys Regarding the Eco-Cycle Toilet]

276
00:18:54,090 --> 00:18:56,800
[Goal: 1000 Surveys]
[Current Amount: 148 Surveys]

277
00:18:58,740 --> 00:19:02,980
Speak up if you're also ever in a bind, okay?

278
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,780
Yanagisawa.

279
00:19:18,710 --> 00:19:20,590
It's about those surveys.

280
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:24,000
I'm sorry.

281
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,740
I need you to help me gather the information we need.

282
00:19:28,060 --> 00:19:35,560
I really... really want this project to succeed.

283
00:19:41,130 --> 00:19:44,000
Sorry, I know you're busy.

284
00:19:44,990 --> 00:19:46,730
That's all I wanted to ask.

285
00:19:46,730 --> 00:19:48,600
I already have them.

286
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:54,940
I have the surveys.

287
00:19:54,940 --> 00:19:57,480
- What?
- I just finished typing them all up.

288
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:59,350
I was about to bring them over to you.

289
00:19:59,350 --> 00:20:01,600
[882 Surveys]

290
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:08,010
That should be enough for the goal of a thousand, right?

291
00:20:19,650 --> 00:20:22,680
Minamikawa asked me to help.

292
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,810
She did?

293
00:20:23,810 --> 00:20:27,650
Yeah. I've never seen her act so sincere.

294
00:20:27,650 --> 00:20:30,350
She really wanted me to lend you a hand.

295
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:32,240
So I gave it a go.

296
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:36,740
This is an amazing feat.

297
00:20:36,740 --> 00:20:39,140
- Thank you.
- Please, don't mention it.

298
00:20:40,300 --> 00:20:42,040
Minamikawa.

299
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:50,000
The surveys... thank you.

300
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:55,080
- I can't thank you enough.
- It was tough work scrounging those up, you know?

301
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,870
And it wasn't just people in the company who helped.

302
00:20:56,870 --> 00:20:59,780
Minato and Tsubaki lent a hand, too.

303
00:20:59,780 --> 00:21:01,440
What?

304
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:03,470
They did?

305
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:05,540
Yes, sir.

306
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:07,150
Wow...

307
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:14,180
Some people think your hard work ethic is annoying.

308
00:21:14,180 --> 00:21:17,640
But I couldn't stand to watch your efforts go to waste.

309
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:25,020
You've always given me the push to do better, sir.

310
00:21:27,380 --> 00:21:34,190
That's why I think you're not so bad after all.

311
00:21:38,970 --> 00:21:40,640
The feeling's mutual.

312
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:46,850
I think you're just as amazing, Minamikawa.

313
00:21:52,060 --> 00:21:54,060
Alright, that's it.

314
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:04,330
You'll have the privilege to work as my subordinate for life.

315
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:05,840
Sorry, what?

316
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:09,000
I'm your junior, not your subordinate.

317
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,750
Thank you for your help, seriously.

318
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:13,660
Thank you.

319
00:22:13,660 --> 00:22:15,600
This is just perfect.

320
00:22:18,190 --> 00:22:20,000
Minamikawa.

321
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Thank you.

322
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,300
Alright!

323
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:25,820
Let's do this.

324
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:29,420
Curse you, Ebikatsu...

325
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,950
Work as his subordinate, for life?

326
00:22:32,950 --> 00:22:34,340
That's Katsuo for you.

327
00:22:34,340 --> 00:22:36,880
I seriously could not believe him.

328
00:22:36,880 --> 00:22:39,750
On that note, thank you for helping with those surveys.

329
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:42,460
I didn't do much. I just passed them out to my customers.

330
00:22:42,460 --> 00:22:45,650
That's more than enough.

331
00:22:46,450 --> 00:22:50,530
I hope Mr. Ebihara's presentation proves to be a success.

332
00:22:51,990 --> 00:22:54,300
And you're fine with this outcome, Amina?

333
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:58,390
- Huh?
- You like Katsuo, don't you?

334
00:22:58,390 --> 00:23:02,730
Of course not. That dense, blockhead is not my type at all.

335
00:23:02,730 --> 00:23:05,010
How scathing.

336
00:23:05,590 --> 00:23:09,760
I envy him, that's all.

337
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:15,220
See, I broke up with my previous ex over something stupid.

338
00:23:15,220 --> 00:23:17,220
"Stupid"?

339
00:23:17,820 --> 00:23:20,970
Smoking's a no-go for me in a relationship,

340
00:23:20,970 --> 00:23:23,450
because my father passed away from lung cancer.

341
00:23:23,450 --> 00:23:26,690
My boyfriend at the time said he'd quit for me,

342
00:23:26,690 --> 00:23:28,900
but he was actually smoking behind my back.

343
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:34,270
When I realized he would never change himself for me,
I lost heart.

344
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:42,080
Ever since then, I thought change was impossible for people.

345
00:23:43,100 --> 00:23:50,120
But watching Mr. Ebihara makes me want to believe again.

346
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:56,040
Maybe change is possible, albeit with time and patience.

347
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:02,550
Sorry, didn't mean to talk about something so stupid.

348
00:24:02,550 --> 00:24:05,060
It's not stupid.

349
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:09,260
- Huh?
- This is clearly an important topic for you.

350
00:24:09,260 --> 00:24:11,670
It's not stupid at all.

351
00:24:13,470 --> 00:24:17,800
Besides, I also feel the same way when I watch Ayu.

352
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:21,830
She makes me believe change is possible for people.

353
00:24:31,670 --> 00:24:34,760
- That's good.
- Right?

354
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:39,210
Vegetables and dough...

355
00:24:39,210 --> 00:24:43,600
With the sauce, that's 250 yen per dish.

356
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,960
[How much will one customer buy?]

357
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:46,410
Which means I should sell for...

358
00:24:46,410 --> 00:24:48,380
[Make sure to treasure your regulars and repeat customers!]

359
00:24:49,150 --> 00:24:52,890
500 Yen.

360
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:56,150
"I am quite interested".

361
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,680
"It would help if I could see the remaining quantities".

362
00:25:05,660 --> 00:25:09,650
How many hours do I need to work?

363
00:25:11,220 --> 00:25:15,060
I still won't have anywhere near enough money.

364
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:24,960
"It depends on"...

365
00:25:37,450 --> 00:25:39,200
I'll help.

366
00:25:46,250 --> 00:25:47,900
Thanks.

367
00:25:49,990 --> 00:25:52,190
- I'm back.
- Welcome back.

368
00:25:54,560 --> 00:25:56,970
Phew, I'm beat.

369
00:25:56,970 --> 00:25:58,370
Do you want to eat dinner now?

370
00:25:58,370 --> 00:26:00,660
Yeah, I'd appreciate that.

371
00:26:11,210 --> 00:26:13,160
What's all this?

372
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:18,390
I was running calculations for initial costs and other expenses.

373
00:26:19,510 --> 00:26:21,340
I see.

374
00:26:22,730 --> 00:26:25,740
Makes sense.

375
00:26:25,740 --> 00:26:27,980
Looks correct.

376
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:30,730
Ayumi, shall I run these calculations for you?

377
00:26:30,730 --> 00:26:32,560
It's fine, I'll do it myself.

378
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:36,410
But this is totally my area of expertise.

379
00:26:36,410 --> 00:26:41,920
First, let's talk break-even point and cost rates.

380
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:44,470
Your cost rates shouldn't go over 30%.

381
00:26:44,470 --> 00:26:47,930
- But for your needs and purposes -
- It's fine.

382
00:26:47,930 --> 00:26:51,440
Katsuo. I want to do this myself.

383
00:26:57,360 --> 00:26:58,870
Sorry.

384
00:27:00,980 --> 00:27:03,860
- I thought you were having trouble.
- I'm not.

385
00:27:06,250 --> 00:27:07,930
I see.

386
00:27:13,120 --> 00:27:16,090
I'm sure this spread is distracting you.

387
00:27:16,090 --> 00:27:18,930
Sorry, I'll run my calculations at home.

388
00:27:37,930 --> 00:27:41,560
You know that guy won't be coming, right?

389
00:27:41,560 --> 00:27:43,280
I know.

390
00:27:43,280 --> 00:27:45,150
Then why wait for him?

391
00:27:45,150 --> 00:27:47,330
You know he won't be here tonight!

392
00:27:47,330 --> 00:27:51,530
I'll always wait for Junpy to come home.

393
00:27:51,530 --> 00:27:53,570
I've already made my choice.

394
00:27:54,610 --> 00:27:56,680
But there's no point.

395
00:27:57,820 --> 00:28:00,890
Why Junpei?

396
00:28:01,610 --> 00:28:03,310
Mari!

397
00:28:14,930 --> 00:28:17,020
Junpy...

398
00:28:29,250 --> 00:28:31,550
I won't be leaving for the Netherlands.

399
00:28:31,550 --> 00:28:34,210
I won't ever leave your side, Mari.

400
00:28:34,210 --> 00:28:38,760
I was so lonely, Junpy.

401
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:41,170
So, so lonely!

402
00:28:43,870 --> 00:28:47,680
Mari, I'm home!

403
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:51,090
Junpy, welcome home!

404
00:28:51,090 --> 00:28:54,530
Congratulations, you two!

405
00:29:18,650 --> 00:29:20,320
That's good.

406
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:46,210
I have a real passion for cooking.
[Handmade Rice Balls]

407
00:29:46,210 --> 00:29:49,740
However, I have no experience cooking professionally.

408
00:29:49,740 --> 00:29:54,410
We don't allow painted nails or piercings in the kitchen.
Is that fine by you?

409
00:29:54,410 --> 00:29:57,300
Yes, of course.

410
00:29:57,300 --> 00:30:01,010
Congrats on the job, Ayumelo. Cheers!

411
00:30:06,090 --> 00:30:07,400
It's only a part-time gig though.

412
00:30:07,400 --> 00:30:09,390
So? That's better than nothing.

413
00:30:09,390 --> 00:30:10,970
You're inching closer to your dream.

414
00:30:10,970 --> 00:30:15,120
Yeah. I'm still far from my goal, but I'll do my best to save up.

415
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:17,620
Guess that means I can charge high for rent.

416
00:30:17,620 --> 00:30:20,140
Taihei, don't bully her.

417
00:30:20,140 --> 00:30:22,070
Sorry, sorry.

418
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:26,980
How did Katsuo react? I bet he was over the moon.

419
00:30:26,980 --> 00:30:29,090
Yeah, he was.

420
00:30:29,090 --> 00:30:31,070
I feel like he'd literally jump for joy.

421
00:30:31,070 --> 00:30:33,290
- Or he'd break out into dance.
- I can see that.

422
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:34,350
Right?

423
00:30:34,350 --> 00:30:37,110
I remember he danced with his hips.

424
00:30:37,110 --> 00:30:39,290
- Like this, I think?
- Yeah, something like that.

425
00:30:40,190 --> 00:30:43,720
I know it's been difficult, but great work so far, Katsuo.

426
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:46,030
Tonight's my treat, alright?

427
00:30:47,190 --> 00:30:48,870
Thanks, Chief.

428
00:30:48,870 --> 00:30:51,650
So this is Minamikawa's go-to spot?

429
00:30:51,650 --> 00:30:53,290
No, it's a go-to spot of mine.

430
00:30:53,290 --> 00:30:54,950
Is that so?

431
00:30:54,950 --> 00:30:58,630
- Your pork jowl.
- Thanks a million.

432
00:31:05,630 --> 00:31:07,560
- What?
- Jowl tastes better straight.

433
00:31:07,560 --> 00:31:10,480
Let people eat however they want.

434
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:13,590
I find it easier, and tastier to eat it this way.

435
00:31:20,750 --> 00:31:22,980
You've changed, Ebihara.

436
00:31:23,620 --> 00:31:25,250
- You think so?
- Yeah.

437
00:31:25,250 --> 00:31:26,800
You've become more sure of yourself.

438
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:28,800
And to that, I say bravo!

439
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:31,290
- Did you want anything to drink?
- No, I'm fine.

440
00:32:31,290 --> 00:32:33,630
Actually...

441
00:32:33,630 --> 00:32:35,160
Could I have a beer?

442
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:39,190
A beer? Sure thing.

443
00:32:42,130 --> 00:32:45,620
And the hairdresser who worked on me instead, was Nagisa.

444
00:32:45,620 --> 00:32:47,230
So that's how you two met.

445
00:32:47,230 --> 00:32:49,330
I remember being surprised by how blunt she was!

446
00:32:49,330 --> 00:32:52,820
Her alien-colored hair shocked me, too.

447
00:32:52,820 --> 00:32:54,500
I don't blame you there.

448
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:58,380
I never thought I'd use a dating app myself.

449
00:32:58,380 --> 00:33:01,640
- And that's how you met Tsubaki?
- Exactly.

450
00:33:05,050 --> 00:33:10,820
So much happened ever since we broke up, huh?

451
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:15,010
Yeah, to the both of us.

452
00:33:16,530 --> 00:33:23,040
Having things the other party doesn't know... isn't so bad, is it?

453
00:33:25,790 --> 00:33:29,300
None of this would have happened
if we stayed together, that's for sure.

454
00:33:32,800 --> 00:33:34,510
Yeah.

455
00:33:39,550 --> 00:33:41,280
Thanks.

456
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:54,220
Listen.

457
00:33:57,480 --> 00:34:04,140
The other day, I had assumed on my own that you needed help.

458
00:34:06,020 --> 00:34:09,380
I overstepped my boundaries without waiting for your answer.

459
00:34:10,490 --> 00:34:12,320
I'm really sorry I encroached on you like that.

460
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:23,810
When you turned down my proposal, I got to thinking.

461
00:34:23,810 --> 00:34:28,600
And at first, I couldn't figure out where I went wrong.

462
00:34:28,600 --> 00:34:31,540
That's why I decided to make chikuzenni.

463
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:35,950
Is that why you asked for my recipe?

464
00:34:35,950 --> 00:34:38,020
Yeah, that's exactly it.

465
00:34:38,020 --> 00:34:41,070
As you can probably guess, my first try was a disaster.

466
00:34:41,070 --> 00:34:44,580
By the time I realized I was missing the stock,
it was already midnight.

467
00:34:44,580 --> 00:34:46,300
I also cut my finger carving the carrots into flowers.

468
00:34:46,300 --> 00:34:49,290
What? You tried that on your first pass? You didn't need to.

469
00:34:49,290 --> 00:34:51,520
No, but I did.

470
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:57,840
Because it made me realize how amazing you are.

471
00:34:59,700 --> 00:35:02,190
And yet.

472
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:05,130
I used to just...

473
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:09,710
nit-pick about your cooking.

474
00:35:10,530 --> 00:35:14,750
Thinking back now, I'm so embarrassed of my old self.

475
00:35:14,750 --> 00:35:17,150
You should be.

476
00:35:17,150 --> 00:35:19,820
You used to call my spread "too brown".

477
00:35:19,820 --> 00:35:23,430
And you'd point out
how I used the same ingredient in two dishes.

478
00:35:24,180 --> 00:35:28,170
Coming up with nutritious meals that never felt repetitive

479
00:35:28,170 --> 00:35:30,650
was a real ordeal, you know?

480
00:35:31,390 --> 00:35:33,250
I'm so sorry.

481
00:35:36,610 --> 00:35:43,090
But I wasn't able to speak up back then either.

482
00:35:44,450 --> 00:35:50,260
I had assumed you'd dislike a girlfriend who got mad at you.

483
00:35:50,260 --> 00:35:53,760
What? No, of course I wouldn't hate that.

484
00:36:03,270 --> 00:36:05,070
Katsuo.

485
00:36:06,660 --> 00:36:11,950
My whole life, I worked hard to be chosen by someone.

486
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:15,220
I strove to be chosen.

487
00:36:17,950 --> 00:36:22,800
And eventually, I was.

488
00:36:23,470 --> 00:36:28,710
Except, then I gave up communicating with my partner.

489
00:36:28,710 --> 00:36:34,300
I never even gave conversation a chance.

490
00:36:37,860 --> 00:36:43,720
So the reason why our relationship was built on self-restraint...

491
00:36:47,530 --> 00:36:49,780
was most certainly my fault.

492
00:36:51,630 --> 00:36:57,120
To be honest, I feel sick with worry.

493
00:36:58,930 --> 00:37:06,150
I'm once again reminded of how terrifying it is
to stand on my own.

494
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:10,510
Relying on another without much thought

495
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:15,440
is definitely the easier option.

496
00:37:20,170 --> 00:37:26,350
But I don't want to learn to stand behind others.

497
00:37:27,810 --> 00:37:30,710
I want to stand next to those individuals, as equals.

498
00:37:34,930 --> 00:37:37,150
So right now...

499
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:42,080
I want to be honest with myself.

500
00:37:43,890 --> 00:37:47,060
I want to be able to stand on my own two feet, alone.

501
00:37:48,810 --> 00:37:51,340
And I want to open that store with my own two hands.

502
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:56,620
I want to do what I can, as the person I am now.

503
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:14,470
Ayumi...

504
00:38:17,530 --> 00:38:21,150
You've helped me time and time again throughout the years.

505
00:38:26,190 --> 00:38:32,840
I think that's why I felt so inclined to help you this time.

506
00:38:35,100 --> 00:38:40,630
But to say I want to support you

507
00:38:42,510 --> 00:38:47,580
when you're trying so hard on your own,
was insensitive, wasn't it?

508
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:57,600
My selfish words and thoughtless actions were putting a lid

509
00:38:59,200 --> 00:39:05,310
on the things you wanted to do, the things you wanted to say.

510
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:17,680
The Katsuo of the past...

511
00:39:18,670 --> 00:39:22,110
would have definitely preferred the Ayumi with black hair.

512
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:26,340
But now I prefer the Ayumi I see in front of me.

513
00:39:26,340 --> 00:39:28,560
This Ayumi is the best.

514
00:39:28,560 --> 00:39:30,230
You're the most beautiful you've ever been.

515
00:39:30,230 --> 00:39:32,440
I mean it.

516
00:39:33,230 --> 00:39:35,560
Truly, from the bottom of my heart, I do.

517
00:39:40,180 --> 00:39:42,420
But the sole reason I can say this...

518
